---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { isBlogPublished } from '../../lib/blogGate';
import BlogCrossLinks from '../../components/BlogCrossLinks.astro';

const slug = Astro.url.pathname.replace('/blog/', '').replace(/\/$/, '');
const isPublished = await isBlogPublished(slug);
if (!isPublished) return Astro.redirect('/404');
---

<Layout title="Cryptocurrency for Beginners: Bitcoin, Ethereum and More" description="Cryptocurrency basics — what Bitcoin and Ethereum are, how they work, and a beginner-friendly introduction to digital currency." keywords="cryptocurrency basics, bitcoin explained, ethereum beginner, what is crypto, digital currency, blockchain basics, crypto for beginners">
  <div class="max-w-3xl">
    <article class="prose dark:prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-amber-600">Blog</a> <span class="mx-1">›</span> <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">Currency</span>
      </nav>
      <BlogCrossLinks title="Cryptocurrency for Beginners: Bitcoin, Ethereum and More" />
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8">July 8, 2025 • 5 min read</p>

      <p>Cryptocurrency is everywhere in the news, but the jargon around it — blockchain, mining, wallets, DeFi — can make it feel impenetrable. Here is a plain-language introduction to digital currencies and how they work.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-1">What is Cryptocurrency?</h2>
      <p>A cryptocurrency is digital money that uses cryptography (mathematical codes) to secure transactions. Unlike traditional currencies issued by governments (USD, EUR, GBP), cryptocurrencies are typically:</p>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Decentralised:</strong> Not controlled by any single government or bank</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Transparent:</strong> All transactions are recorded on a public ledger (blockchain)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Limited supply:</strong> Most have a maximum number of coins that can ever exist</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Digital-only:</strong> No physical coins or notes</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-1">The Major Cryptocurrencies</h2>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Bitcoin (BTC):</strong> The original cryptocurrency (2009). Digital gold — primarily used as a store of value. Maximum supply: 21 million coins</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Ethereum (ETH):</strong> A programmable blockchain (2015). Powers smart contracts and decentralised applications. Used for NFTs, DeFi, and more</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Stablecoins (USDT, USDC):</strong> Pegged to traditional currencies (usually $1 each). Used for trading and transfers without volatility</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Others:</strong> Thousands exist with different purposes — payments, privacy, gaming, data storage</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-1">How Does Blockchain Work?</h2>
      <p>Think of a blockchain as a shared spreadsheet that thousands of computers maintain simultaneously:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>You send crypto to someone — this creates a transaction</li>
        <li>The transaction is broadcast to a network of computers (nodes)</li>
        <li>Nodes verify the transaction is valid (you have sufficient funds, no double-spending)</li>
        <li>Verified transactions are grouped into a "block"</li>
        <li>The block is added to the chain permanently — it cannot be altered or deleted</li>
      </ol>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-1">Key Concepts for Beginners</h2>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Wallet:</strong> Software that stores your crypto keys (not the coins themselves — those live on the blockchain)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Private key:</strong> A secret code that proves you own your crypto. Lose it and you lose access forever</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Mining:</strong> Using computers to validate transactions and earn new coins (Bitcoin uses this)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Staking:</strong> Locking up your crypto to help validate transactions and earn rewards (Ethereum uses this)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Exchange:</strong> A platform where you buy, sell, and trade cryptocurrencies</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-1">Risks to Understand</h2>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Volatility:</strong> Prices can swing 10-20% in a single day</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>No guarantees:</strong> Unlike bank deposits, crypto is not insured or guaranteed</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Scams:</strong> The space attracts fraudsters — never share your private keys</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Regulation:</strong> Laws around crypto vary by country and are still evolving</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Complexity:</strong> Mistakes (wrong address, lost keys) are usually irreversible</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p>Cryptocurrency is a rapidly evolving space. Whether you choose to invest or not, understanding the basics helps you make informed decisions in an increasingly digital financial world.</p>

      <div class="border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 mt-10 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Try It Now</h3>
        <a href="/tools/crypto-coins" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-amber-500 text-white text-sm font-semibold hover:bg-amber-600 transition-colors">Open Crypto Tracker →</a>
      </div>
    
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 p-4 bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl">
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-300 font-medium">🔗 Try our converter: <a href="/tools/crypto-coins" class="text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 font-bold hover:underline">Open Tool →</a></p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</Layout>
